text: Patagoniodes farinaria, the blue stem borer, is a moth of the family Pyralidae. It is found in New Zealand and Australia. It is a shoot borer that feeds on Senecio jacobaea, Senecio species and closely related plants. ==References== Category:Moths of New Zealand Category:Moths of Australia ==External links== Wikimedia Commons: Patagoniodes farinaria
